<p>A <b>farcaster</b> is an <a href="/wiki/Teleportation" title="Teleportation">instantaneous transportation device</a> in the fictional <a href="/wiki/Hyperion_Cantos" title="Hyperion Cantos">Hyperion</a> universe. Farcasters allow two points separated by a vast distance to be brought together at a Farcaster Portal. The Farcaster network connects hundreds of planets of the Hegemony of Man into their WorldWeb. The Farcaster network allowed transport between connected worlds without any time discrepancy, unlike <a href="/wiki/Hawking_drive" title="Hawking drive" class="mw-redirect">Hawking drive</a> (<a href="/wiki/Faster-than-light" title="Faster-than-light">FTL</a> - faster than light) transport provided by spaceships of the Hegemony era. The Farcaster was developed by the <a href="/wiki/Artificial_intelligence" title="Artificial intelligence">Artificial Intelligences</a> (AIs) of the <a href="/wiki/Technocore" title="Technocore" class="mw-redirect">TechnoCore</a> and given to humanity sometime after the Hegira.</p>
<p>It was the destruction of the Farcaster network at the order of Hegemony CEO Meina Gladstone in 2852 which precipitated the Fall.</p>
<p></p>
